    "body": "Fixes #35250.\\n\\nThis keeps MuSig2 secnonces keyed by both the session id and the generated public nonce, so re-processing the same nonce-less PSBT starts another signing session instead of replacing or asserting on the existing one. Signing later looks up the secnonce matching the pubnonce present in the PSBT and deletes only that session after use.\\n\\nTests:\\n- cmake --build build-depends -t test_bitcoin -j\"$(nproc)\"\\n- build-depends/bin/test_bitcoin --run_test=psbt_wallet_tests --catch_system_errors=no --log_level=test_suite\\n- cmake --build build-depends -t bitcoind bitcoin-cli -j\"$(nproc)\"\\n- python3 build-depends/test/functional/test_runner.py --jobs=1 wallet_musig.py",
    "labels": [
